## Pairing with API errors

For toast / inline error copy, prefer i18n keys first; fall back to
`ErrorMessages[code]` only when no key exists for that error.

```typescript
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';
import { ApiError } from '@/lib/api/client';
import { ErrorCode, ErrorMessages } from '@/lib/api/response';

const t = useTranslations('errors'); // top of component

try {
  await callApi('/endpoint', body);
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof ApiError) {
    const localized =
      err.code === ErrorCode.INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS
        ? t('insufficientCredits')
        : (ErrorMessages[err.code] ?? ErrorMessages[ErrorCode.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR]);
    toast.error(localized);
  }
}
```

See `api-request-state-management.mdc` for the full lifecycle.

