## Routing

`src/i18n/routing.ts` exports typed `Link`, `useRouter`, `usePathname`,
`getPathname`, and `redirect`. Use these wherever you'd otherwise import
from `next/link` or `next/navigation` for **internal** navigation.

```typescript
// ✅ Locale-aware
import { Link, useRouter } from '@/i18n/routing';

<Link href="/app/projects">My Projects</Link>;
const router = useRouter();
router.push('/app/projects');

// ❌ Drops the [locale] segment
import Link from 'next/link';
<Link href="/app/projects">...</Link>;
```

External links (`https://...`) and same-document anchors (`#section`) are
fine via plain `<a>` / `next/link`.

---

## Locale-file parity

When you add a key to `messages/en.json`, you MUST add the same key path
to `messages/zh.json` in the same edit. If a translation isn't ready,
ship the English copy as the placeholder so the user sees something
intelligible — never leave the key missing.

```jsonc
// messages/en.json
{ "projects": { "title": "Projects", "newButton": "New project" } }

// messages/zh.json — same shape, translated values
{ "projects": { "title": "项目",     "newButton": "新建项目" } }
```

A grep is enough to catch one-side drift before committing:

```bash
# Quick parity smoke (top-level keys only)
diff <(jq 'paths(scalars) | join(".")' messages/en.json | sort) \
     <(jq 'paths(scalars) | join(".")' messages/zh.json | sort)
```

---

## Checklist

- [ ] No hardcoded user-facing English / 中文 in JSX or toasts
- [ ] `useTranslations` (client) or `getTranslations` (server) chosen correctly
- [ ] Hook called at the top of the component, never in handlers
- [ ] Internal navigation uses helpers from `@/i18n/routing` (not `next/link`)
- [ ] Every new key exists in both `messages/en.json` and `messages/zh.json`
- [ ] Comments, logs, and LLM prompts remain in English
- [ ] Dynamic metadata uses `getTranslations({ locale, namespace })`
